(87101, 'the website runs in a lamp environment and is highly optimized by several bash scripts                    ul                    lione is run from a cron to use imagemagick for cropping and resizing images based on automated cue table maintained when a size or shape is requested that has not yet been cutli                    lianother is for reindexing the music catalogue  of 20000 songs and growing it extends a tool called beets to correct mp3 metadata download artwork and lyrics and determine soundwave averages such as bpm beatsperminute and replay gain used to determine average encoded decibel volume of the sound waveli                    lithe backend system also includes an asynchronous email service which i linked seamlessly to the frontend webpage templates with a css inliner scriptli                    lithe site scales very well to all screen widths above 320 pixels wide but i am well underway with a native android version of the player with 0100 scale music ratings to refine the rotation of songsli                    liit also includes a codeigniter plugin that manages translations of system copy and usergenerated content with version controlling text changes by authorized userauthorsli                ul', 'ugc', 'C:\\DATA\\TaylorMade\\tmt\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 128, '/eli', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', 'The website runs in a LAMP environment, and is highly optimized by several Bash scripts\n                    <ul>\n                    <li>One is run from a CRON to use ImageMagick for cropping and resizing images based on automated cue table maintained when a size or shape is requested that has not yet been cut.</li>\n                    <li>Another is for re-indexing the music catalogue - of 20,000 songs and growing. It extends a tool called Beets to correct mp3 meta-data, download artwork and lyrics, and determine sound-wave averages such as BPM (beats-per-minute) and Replay Gain (used to determine average encoded decibe