(87095, 'another quick campaign application to generate fanpage likes to compete users were required to like sedals fanpage complete regisration and upload videos images or a tip on maintaining their hair ideally using sedal products voting was validated by ip user agent and php session while video uploads were posted directly to a public youtube channel using their php sdk the project extended ids fork of the slim php framework i personally found more hurdles than helpers in the tightly namespaced codebase and odd use of closures for routingcontrollers', 'ugc', 'C:\\DATA\\TaylorMade\\tmt\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 128, '/eli', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', 'Another quick campaign application to generate FanPage likes. To compete users were required to like Sedal''s FanPage, complete regisration, and upload videos, images, or a tip on maintaining their hair (ideally using Sedal products;). Voting was validated by IP, user agent, and PHP session, while video uploads were POSTed directly to a public YouTube channel using their PHP SDK. The project extended ID''s fork of the Slim PHP Framework. I personally found more hurdles than helpers in the tightly namespaced codebase and odd use of closures for routing/controllers.', NULL, 'es', 'debug', NULL, 1389597303, '2014-01-12 23:33:43'),
(87087, 'pbelow are a few of the projects ive built over the past decade my role and the a hrefteamteam membersa whom i can remember are tagged along with the a hreftechnologiestechnologiesa that were used if you have a project in mind and want to find my similar experiences than filter by clicking the tagsppi am currently focused on building mobile applications around music art and education however even in developing the driest of subjects  automated healthcare advertising  ive found fun in problem solving and strategyi have developed for all ends of the stack but my strongest expertise is in desktopstyle interface engineering such as browser plugins heavyajax sites and mobile applicationsppim always available via email span classalinkeattaylormadetrafficcomspanp', 'ugc', 'C:\\DATA\\TaylorMade\\tmt\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 22, '/eli', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', '<p>Below are a few of the projects I''ve built over the past decade. My role and the <a href=''/team''>team members</a> whom I can remember are tagged along with the <a href=''/technologies''>technologies</a> that were used. If you have a project in mind and want to find my similar experiences than filter by clicking the tags.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am currently focused on building mobile applications around music, art, and education. However, even in developing the driest of subjects - automated healthcare advertising - I''ve found fun in problem solving and strategy.\r\n\r\n\r\nI have developed for all ends of the stack, but my strongest expertise is in desktop-style interface engineering, such as browser plugins, heavy-ajax sites, and mobile applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I''m always available via email: <span class=''alink''>eat@taylormadetraffic.com</span></p>', NULL, 'es', 'debug', NULL, 1389597303, '2014-01-12 23:33:43'),
(87088, 'idinteractive builds marketing platforms for a long list of great clients with creative projects and campaigns one of the most fun i built in a quick 4 weeks was  the campaign was based on 20 million codes printed on oreo packages throughout colombia there were 5 types of prizes to win in varying amounts with a total of 285 to give  no one code could be considered a winner in advance and the prizes should be distributed evenly throughout the 60 day campaign i wrote the probability to be related to the average number of people playing daily and distributed all prizes  by number and type  evenly until the last day', 'ugc', 'C:\\DATA\\TaylorMade\\tmt\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 127, '/eli', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', 'IDinteractive builds marketing platforms for a long list of great clients with creative projects and campaigns. One of the most fun I built in a quick 4 weeks was . The campaign was based on 20 million codes printed on Oreo packages throughout Colombia. There were 5 types of prizes to win in varying amounts with a total of 285 to give.  No one code could be considered a winner in advance, and the prizes should be distributed evenly throughout the ~60 day campaign. I wrote the probability to be related to the average number of people playing daily and distributed all prizes - by number and type – evenly until the last day.', NULL, 'es', 'debug', NULL, 1389597303, '2014-01-12 23:33:43'),
